{{Infobox Website | name = ''4player'' | logo = 4player.de_logo.png | screenshot = | caption = | url = www.4players.de/ | type = [[Video game]] [[website]] | registration = | owner = [[Computec Media GmbH]] | launch date = May, 2000 | current status = Active | alexa = {{increaseNegative}} 17,113 ({{as of|2016|6|10|alt= June 2016}})<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/4players.de|title= 4players.de Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] | accessdate= 10 June 2016 }}</ref> }}
'''''4players''''' is a major German online magazine which provides news and reviews of [[video game]]s and related content.
==History== ''4players'' was founded in May 2000 by the active newmedia GmbH agency in collaboration with the [[Freenet AG]]. It was created to provide reviews and news in the video gaming world. The new online portal was then put under the ownership of the freeXmedia GmbH. In December 2014, the portal was bought by the Computec Media GmbH, which already owns a gaming and PC network with outlets like [[PC Games (magazine)|PC Games]], [[Buffed.de|Buffed]] or [[Golem.de]].<ref name="freenet">{{cite web|url=https://www.heise.de/newsticker/meldung/Freenet-trennt-sich-von-zwei-Toechtern-1762179.html|title=Freenet trennt sich von zwei Töchtern|language=German|accessdate=4 October 2016|author=Volker Briegleb|publisher=[[Heinz Heise|Heise Online]]|website=heise.de}}</ref><ref name="gamestar">{{cite web|url= http://www.gamestar.de/news/branche/3007346/4playersde.html|title=4Players.de - PC Games-Verlag Computec übernimmt Website|author1=Rene Heuser|author2=André Peschke |publisher=[[Gamestar]]|website=gamestar.de|language=German|accessdate=4 October 2016}}</ref>
As of June 2016, general chief is Mathias Oertel and editor in chief is Jörg Luibl.<ref name="team">{{cite web|url=http://www.4players.de/4players.php/company_info/-/index.html|title=4players.de team|accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref>
==Features== ''4players'' provides news, reviews and downloads for various video games platform. The mainpage is split into sections for every platform the portal covers: PC, [[PS4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Wii U]], [[virtual reality|VR]] and [[mobile gaming|handhelds]]. Additionally ''4players'' providers coverage around the general video games community, [[eSports]], a tips section, an internet forum as well as a video section with video reviews.<ref name="web">{{cite web|url=http://www.4players.de|title=4players.de mainpage|accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref> The portal also provides additional features such as an iPhone and android app as well as a [[teamspeak]] server service.<ref name="teamspeak">{{cite web|url= http://www.4players.de/teamspeak3/ts3-server-mieten|title=4players.de teamspeak service|accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=digkiosk>{{cite magazine |last=Barczok |first=Achim |date=October 2014 |title=Der digitale Kiosk |url=https://shop.heise.de/katalog/der-digitale-kiosk |magazine=[[c't|c't – Magazin für Computertechnik]] |language=German |publisher=[[Heinz Heise|Verlag Heinz Heise]] |access-date=4 October 2016 }}</ref>
==Reception== As of February 2016, ''4players.de'' was one of the largest German online video gaming portals, with about 7 million page impressions and 801.000 unique visits per month.<ref name="stats">{{cite web|url=https://www.agof.de/download/Downloads_digital_facts/Downloads_Digital_Facts_2016/Downloads_Digital_Facts_2016-02/02-2016_df_Ranking_Gesamtangebote_Internet.pdf?e6c0a9|title=AGOF digital facts: website statistics February 2016 |publisher={{Interlanguage link multi|Arbeitsgemeinschaft Online Forschung|de}}|website=agof.de|accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref>
In 2008, ''4Players'' was one of the main reviewers of Atari's new game ''[[Alone in the Dark (2008 video game)|Alone in the Dark]]'' which were threatened with legal action after they gave the game a mediocre rating. ''4Players'' was accused of obtaining an illegal version of the game before it was released and Atari wanted to force ''4Players'' to pull the review from their webpage. At the same time Atari also cancelled an advertising campaign on the ''4Players'' website, which was interpreted as applying further pressure on the online portal. This garnered an enormous media echo nationally and internationally, which forced Atari to row back on its demands and both ''4Players'' and Atari were able to settle differences out of court.<ref name="sue">{{cite web|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/digital/computerspiele-industrie-spieleriese-gibt-klein-bei-1.197319|title=Spieleriese gibt klein bei|language=German|accessdate=4 October 2016|author=Sarina Märschel|publisher=[[Süddeutsche Zeitung]]|website=sueddeutsche.de}}</ref><ref name="kotaku">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5018149/legal-mess-over-euro-alone-in-the-dark-reviews-update|title=Legal Mess Over Euro Alone In The Dark Reviews|accessdate=4 October 2016|author=Luke Plunkett|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|website=kotaku.com}}</ref><ref name="spiegel">{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/netzwelt/spielzeug/per-anwalt-gegen-kritiken-spieleindustrie-setzt-fachpresse-unter-druck-a-561478.html|title=Spieleindustrie setzt Fachpresse unter Druck|language=German|accessdate=4 October 2016|author=Christian Stöcker|publisher=[[Spiegel Online]]|website=spiegel.de}}</ref>
